{"type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Hybrid — Layer Backend + Domain Frontend\n      Konsep: Backend pakai layer-based (commands/, db/ sub-modules) karena Rust module system cocok. Frontend pakai domain-based grouping (features/ atau domain folders) + shared primitives. Best of both worlds.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Backend tetap idiomatic Rust — commands/mod.rs re-exports, db/repos terpisah\n            Frontend components grouped by feature — easy to find related UI\n            Shared UI primitives + hooks extracted ke common layer\n            Pragmatic — follows how each stack naturally organizes\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Dua mental models — perlu tahu backend = by layer, frontend = by domain\n            Slightly more planning needed for the boundary\n          \n        \n      \n      \n        Rekomendasi gue. Rust module system works best with layer separation (commands/, db/). React components work best grouped by feature. Ini approach paling natural untuk Tauri app.","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1776020850085}
